# Add a Form Flow Skill (`@tanstack/react-form` + Zod)

The project ships `@tanstack/react-form` and `zod` v4. Do **not** introduce `react-hook-form`.

## 1. Decide the surface

- **Inline form** — short, lives on its own page (sign-in, contact). Pattern below.
- **Modal form** — short, lives next to a list. Wrap in shadcn `Dialog` (install via `yarn dlx shadcn@latest add dialog`).
- **Multi-step / page form** — split each step into its own component; share form state via the `react-form` `useForm` instance lifted to the parent.

## 2. Schema first

Define the Zod schema next to the form (or in `src/lib/schemas/<feature>.schema.ts` when shared):

```ts
import { z } from 'zod'

export const loginSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email('Enter a valid email'),
  password: z.string().min(8, 'At least 8 characters'),
})

export type LoginInput = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>
```

Rules:

- Schema is the **single source of truth**. Component types come from `z.infer<typeof schema>`.
- Per-field error messages live in the schema (second arg to validators) — don't duplicate them in the component.

## 3. Build the form

```tsx
import { useForm } from '@tanstack/react-form'
import type { LoginInput } from '#/lib/schemas/login.schema'
import { loginSchema } from '#/lib/schemas/login.schema'

type Props = {
  onSubmit: (values: LoginInput) => Promise<void>
  isPending?: boolean
}

export function LoginForm({ onSubmit, isPending }: Props) {
  const form = useForm({
    defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' } as LoginInput,
    validators: { onSubmit: loginSchema },
    onSubmit: async ({ value }) => {
      await onSubmit(value)
    },
  })

  return (
    <form
      noValidate
      onSubmit={(e) => {
        e.preventDefault()
        e.stopPropagation()
        void form.handleSubmit()
      }}
      className="space-y-4"
    >
      <form.Field
        name="email"
        validators={{ onChange: loginSchema.shape.email }}
        children={(field) => (
          <div className="space-y-1">
            <label htmlFor={field.name} className="text-sm font-medium">
              Email
            </label>
            <input
              id={field.name}
              name={field.name}
              type="email"
              autoComplete="email"
              value={field.state.value}
              onBlur={field.handleBlur}
              onChange={(e) => field.handleChange(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full rounded-md border border-input bg-background px-3 py-2 text-sm"
            />
            {field.state.meta.isTouched && field.state.meta.errors.length > 0 ? (
              <p className="text-xs text-destructive">{String(field.state.meta.errors[0])}</p>
            ) : null}
          </div>
        )}
      />

      <form.Field
        name="password"
        validators={{ onChange: loginSchema.shape.password }}
        children={(field) => (
          <div className="space-y-1">
            <label htmlFor={field.name} className="text-sm font-medium">
              Password
            </label>
            <input
              id={field.name}
              name={field.name}
              type="password"
              autoComplete="current-password"
              value={field.state.value}
              onBlur={field.handleBlur}
              onChange={(e) => field.handleChange(e.target.value)}
              className="w-full rounded-md border border-input bg-background px-3 py-2 text-sm"
            />
            {field.state.meta.isTouched && field.state.meta.errors.length > 0 ? (
              <p className="text-xs text-destructive">{String(field.state.meta.errors[0])}</p>
            ) : null}
          </div>
        )}
      />

      <button
        type="submit"
        disabled={isPending || form.state.isSubmitting}
        className="w-full rounded-md bg-primary px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground disabled:opacity-50"
      >
        {isPending || form.state.isSubmitting ? 'Signing in…' : 'Sign in'}
      </button>
    </form>
  )
}
```

What to notice:

- `validators.onSubmit: loginSchema` runs the whole schema on submit; `onChange: loginSchema.shape.<field>` runs the per-field validator on every change.
- The component is presentational: it receives `onSubmit` and `isPending` from the parent.
- Token utilities (`bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`, `border-input`, `bg-background`) — no hex.

## 4. Wire to a server function (optional)

```tsx
// route file
import { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'
import { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'
import { useState } from 'react'

import { LoginForm } from './-components/login-form'
import { loginSchema } from '#/lib/schemas/login.schema'

const login = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })
  .validator(loginSchema.parse)
  .handler(async ({ data }) => {
    // call backend, set cookies, etc.
    return { ok: true as const }
  })

export const Route = createFileRoute('/login')({ component: LoginPage })

function LoginPage() {
  const [isPending, setPending] = useState(false)

  return (
    <LoginForm
      isPending={isPending}
      onSubmit={async (values) => {
        try {
          setPending(true)
          await login({ data: values })
        } finally {
          setPending(false)
        }
      }}
    />
  )
}
```

- The server function re-validates with Zod inside `.validator(...)`. Trust nothing client-sent.
- Co-located route components live in a `<route>.-components/` folder (the `-` prefix excludes the file from the router's automatic file-based detection while still keeping it next to the route).

## 5. shadcn Form primitives (when installed)

Once `yarn dlx shadcn@latest add form input label button` has been run, replace the raw `<input>` / `<label>` / `<button>` with the shadcn primitives — they bring built-in error rendering and accessible labelling. Keep the `react-form` field wiring; only swap the rendered DOM.

## Acceptance checklist

- [ ] Zod schema is the single source of truth; types via `z.infer`.
- [ ] No `react-hook-form` import.
- [ ] Form submission re-validates on the server (when a server function is involved).
- [ ] Submit button is disabled while submitting / pending.
- [ ] Per-field error messages come from the schema, not hardcoded in the component.
- [ ] Token utilities used for colour / border (`bg-primary`, `border-input`, etc.).
- [ ] No floating promises in submit handlers.
